This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentiment classification. The paper also proposes a novel model for this task, which involves attention mechanisms and interactive learning, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of representations and modeling, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
